---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How MoveWell Reviews collects, uses, and protects your information.">
  <article class="container legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

    <p class="notice">
      This page is a starting template, not legal advice. Have a qualified attorney review it
      before launch, especially once you add specific analytics, ad networks, or email tools —
      each has its own required disclosures.
    </p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} ({SITE.domain}) publishes reviews and buying guides for walking pads and
      recovery equipment. This policy explains what information we collect when you visit, and
      how we use it.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, referring site, device/browser type, and approximate location (via IP), collected through analytics.</li>
      <li><strong>Newsletter signups:</strong> your email address, if you voluntarily subscribe.</li>
      <li><strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> your name, email, and message, if you contact us.</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate click data:</strong> which outbound affiliate links were clicked and from which page, so we can understand which content is useful. We do not log this data with any information that identifies you personally.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not knowingly collect payment information, passwords, or government ID numbers — we never ask for them.</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use minimal cookies/local storage to remember your cookie-consent choice and, if enabled,
      privacy-respecting analytics. You can control cookies through your browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To operate and improve the site (understand what content is useful).</li>
      <li>To send newsletter emails, only if you opted in, and to let you unsubscribe at any time.</li>
      <li>To respond to messages sent through our contact form.</li>
      <li>To measure which affiliate links perform well, in aggregate, without linking clicks to your identity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>
      We link to third-party retailers and brands (such as Amazon.com) through affiliate links —
      see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>. Once you click through to
      a third-party site, that site's own privacy policy applies, not ours. We may use third-party
      service providers for hosting (Netlify), database (Supabase), and analytics; these providers
      process data on our behalf under their own security practices.
    </p>

    <h2>Your privacy choices (California — CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
    <p>
      If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we
      collect, request deletion of your personal information, and opt out of the "sale" or
      "sharing" of personal information for cross-context behavioral advertising, if applicable.
      {SITE.name} does not sell personal information for money. If we ever use advertising
      partners that share data for interest-based ads, we will provide a
      "Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information" link here. To exercise any of these rights,
      <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Other regions (GDPR)</h2>
    <p>
      If you are visiting from the EU/UK, you may have additional rights under GDPR, including
      access, correction, deletion, and portability of your data. Contact us to exercise these
      rights.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      This site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
      information from children under 13, in accordance with COPPA.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention &amp; security</h2>
    <p>
      We retain newsletter and contact data only as long as needed for the purposes above, and
      use reasonable technical safeguards (access-controlled database, encrypted connections) to
      protect it. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects
      the most recent revision.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy or a data request? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>
      or use our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: 40px 24px 70px; max-width: 720px; }
  .updated { color: #888; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .notice { background: #fff8e6; border: 1px solid #f0d78c; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  h2 { margin-top: 30px; }
</style>
